 DETAILED OUTLINE OF RESEARCH PROPOSAL Current State of Knowledge Primary liver cancer, hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC), is a major health problem worldwide.

 It is the 5th most common cancer and the 3rd most common cause of cancer death in the world.

 Eighty-five percent of cases occur in developing countries, while in the United States and Canada, it is the fastest growing cancer.

