 For SBRT, advanced techniques are used to very accurately deliver a high total dose to the target in a small number of daily fractions while avoiding dose delivery to surrounding healthy structures.

 SBRT is offered as an ablative radical local treatment.

 In total, eleven primary series reported on tumor response and survival of around 300 patients who have been treated with stereotactic body radiation therapy as primary therapy for HCC.

 The reported percentage of objective responses defined as complete and partial was 64% in 7 of 8 series.

